      "id": "231fa180135b157e",
      "text": "Here we indicate some of the dual/dialectical implications of work oriented design - in dual power, in tradition/transcendence, in designing/curating of commons and in using/enjoying.\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "e94e28429dc414f6",
      "text": " The traditions of ‘work-oriented design’ are directly relevant here. The tradition actually is *work-life* oriented: experiential, situational, in relationship . . in context, *in a process* of making-a-life for individuals and for collectives . . in a continuous balance between tradition and transcendence . . in an aware duality of power *in-and-against* the dominant relations of production. \n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "c86941767bd8c2e9",
      "text": "Tools (infrastructures of tools) need to be designed in ways that facilitate this **awareness** of balance, and furnish affordances for **making** the balance, in plural relationships, in multiple recurring situations, for individuals and for collectives.\n\n\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "aefc2270d2e548b8",
      "text": "The primary vehicle for the awareness, and for the design of affordances into everyday forces of production, is **pattern language**. At the centre of each pattern (in a relational context of *other patterns* which may be ‘completed’ by this one, or which may be needed in order to ‘complete’ the present one) is a conflict or contradiction between possible responses to a situation, and a framing of how that contradiction may be resolved. Such conflicts and contradictions are expressed in terms of dominant relations of production in the landscape of practice, and altered relations of production, which may be established by aware, skilful activists. \n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "f3acf443e751db74",
      "text": "This *in-and-against* framing - the tradition/transcendence options - is the basis, at the level of everyday practice, for the conduct of a practice of **dual power**: production in-and-of commons. \n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "2dade2a7fa2be7f7",
      "text": "Pattern language facilitates both **design/curating** of forces of production (infrastructures, constellations of persons and materials, genres) and their aware, selective **enjoying/mobilising in the moment**. \n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "ab63f98af24354e8",
      "text": "Pattern language and literacy is fundamental, not only for design, but also for **aware conduct** of productive activity; which is to say, any and all activity."
